A construction worker lost a part of his leg in Pretoria North, Gauteng paramedics said on Saturday. The man, believed to be in his thirties, had been cleaning a cement mixer when it turned on, said Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst. The accident happened at a factory in Bon Accord on Friday afternoon. He was rushed to hospital in a helicopter. https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/construction-workers-leg-amputated-in-concrete-mixer-20191005